value.value: An atoll in the North Pacific Ocean near the end of the Hawaiian Archipelago.

Inflammation of the distal posterior uveal tract (choroid) and its structural and vascular attachments to the retina. It is usually caused by infection and though rare, it is clinically significant due to its most serious sequela: loss of vision.
A pump system with one enclosed reservoir, designed to deliver intravenous contrast agent.
Elevated bilirubin levels in the blood of a newborn infant. It is a normal response due to the limited ability to excrete bilirubin until the maturation of the neonatal liver is complete.
A screening test for cognitive impairment that is administered by a non-physician. This test is designed to discriminate between mild, moderate, and severe cognitive deficits.
A question asking an individual to state the current year.
A question asking an individual to state the current month.
A question asking an individual to state the current time, to within 1 hour.
A request that an individual count backwards from 20 to 1.

label.value: Say the Months in Reverse Order

value.value: A request that an individual say the months of the year in reverse order.
A request that an individual repeat a memory phrase.

A laboratory test that estimates kidney function. It is calculated using an individual's serum creatinine measurement, age, gender, and race. Actual results are reported when the estimated glomerular filtration rate is less than 60 ml/min.

Blue skin coloration due to elevated blood levels of methemoglobin. The degree of cyanosis is directly correlated to the concentration of methemoglobin in the blood. As methemoglobin is not suitable for carrying oxygen, hypoxemia becomes a serious sequela.
Symptoms, physical examination results, and/or laboratory rest results related to the muscles and bones.
A disorder characterized by an arrhythmia with an above normal rate.
A newborn reflex that is characterized by flexion of the toes when the sole of the foot is stroked.
Insufficient production of all the anterior pituitary hormones.
An umbilical cyst that arises from allantoic tissue that did not regress during gestational development. Most cases involve a patent urachus that allows for communication to the urinary bladder.
Aberrant drainage of one or more of the pulmonary veins which causes the return of oxygen-rich blood to the right atrium.
Damage to the muscles, bones and their supportive structural attachments.
A pump system with two enclosed reservoirs, designed to deliver various concentrations of intravenous contrast media.
A saline solution used to force an agent from tubing and peripheral veins into the central blood volume.

label.value: Older Americans Resource Scale Multidimensional Functional Assessment Questionnaire

value.value: A questionnaire that seeks information both on a person's level of functioning and on their need and utilization of services.

label.value: Activities of Daily Living Dimension of Functioning Questionnaire

value.value: A section of the Older Americans Resource Scale Multidimensional Functional Assessment Questionnaire (OMFAQ) that seeks information on a person's level of functioning on daily activities of living.
A question about whether an individual is able to use a telephone.

label.value: Get to Places Out of Walking Distance

value.value: A question about whether an individual is able to get to places beyond walking distance.
